    "body": "I was able to make an imperfect fix by printing a character and coloring it. After which, none works.\n\n```toml\nformat = \"\"\"\n${custom.fix}\\\n$shell\\\n....\n\"\"\"\n\n[custom.fix]\nformat = '''[ ]($style)'''\nwhen = true\nstyle = \"8\"\n```\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6569cff2-ff45-4ee1-b4e4-9c2c5bab7632)\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a4424e46-6976-4a88-aa4d-e5668bd6ccbb)\n\n^ style = \"8\" (gray) is somewhat visible on both backgrounds..\n\nThis is imperfect, as the first module can't be set to none - as it per the described issue.\nThis is useful for coloring the module based on the system color scheme:\ndark  background -> light color\nlight background -> dark  color\n\n\n\n\n",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
